        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 3:58PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rock Cave, or 14 miles southwest of Buckhannon, moving northeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Buckhannon, Rock Cave, Alexander, Walkersville, Ellamore, Kanawha
Head, Eden, Tallmansville, Overhill, Alton, French Creek, and
Cleveland.

This includes Route 33 between mile markers 15 and 17.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Charleston West Virginia.</instruction>
